A system includes a memory and a processor. The memory
may store a customer account associated with a customer
and an enterprise account associated with an enterprise. The
processor may be communicatively coupled to the memory
and may cause the system to receive a request to deposit a
first amount of a cryptocurrency in the customer account
from the customer. The processor may also cause the system
to determine a public key associated with the customer
account and receive the first amount of the cryptocurrency.
The processor may further cause the system to determine a
first value approximately equivalent to the first amount of
cryptocurrency and associate the first value with the cus-
tomer account. The processor is further able to aggregate the
first amount of cryptocurrency with an aggregated amount of
the cryptocurrency in the enterprise account and facilitate
securing the public key in the enterprise account.
